				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes, writing to OAM during Hblank goes to:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">uint16 addr = 0x0200 + &#40;last_accessed_sprite_item &gt;&gt; 2&#41;;<br />memory::oam&#91;addr&#93; = &#40;uint8&#41;data;</div>
<br />
<br />As you should know, the extended 32-bytes encode data for four sprites at a time. It control d8 of X and the size of the sprite (small or large.) It's not a very useful thing to be able to write to, but again, Uniracers manages to make use of this. I haven't really bothered to figure out how.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

